## 1. Instructions

### 1.1 Output Language Contract

The project's preferred narrative language is `output_lang` in
`.harness/config.toml` (this project: **`{{ output_lang }}`**;
allowed values: `en`, `zh`). Every `/hx-*` command MUST honor it
when producing **deliverables** that humans on this project will
read — `specs/<NNN>-<slug>/*.md`, `.harness/knowledge/**`,
`.harness/memory/constitution.md`, `.agent/progress.md`,
`session-handoff.md`, review reports, ADRs, and any prose written
*into* an existing file.

The following MUST stay English regardless of `output_lang` — they
are the AI-coding contract that `/hx-review`, `/hx-analyze`,
`/hx-doctor`, `/hx-implement` pattern-match against. Translating
them silently degrades AI accuracy:

- Markdown headings (`#`, `##`, `###`, …) and YAML frontmatter
- `> Provenance` blocks (Authoritative paradigm / Investigation
  protocol / Output form)
- RFC 2119 keywords: **MUST**, **MUST NOT**, **SHOULD**,
  **SHOULD NOT**, **MAY**
- Stable IDs: REQ-NNN, NFR-NNN, IF-NNN, DEC-NNN, RISK-NNN, Q-NNN,
  ADR-NNNN, P1–P5, P-G-N, T1–T16, US-N, T-N.M, feat-NNN
- Methodology and pattern names: Saga, TCC, Outbox, Redlock,
  fencing token, C4, arc42, MADR, BIZBOK, 12-Factor, OWASP,
  AIP, AAA (Arrange · Act · Assert), Expand → Contract, Diátaxis
- Code identifiers, file paths, command names, tool names, flag
  values (e.g. `quick` / `standard` / `full` / `epic`,
  `enforceable` / `inferential`, `ship` / `fix-then-ship`,
  `not-started` / `in-progress` / `passing`)
- JSON keys (e.g. `id`, `status`, `evidence`, `verification`,
  `depends_on`)
- Structural labels inside artifact bodies — `Rule:`, `Why:`,
  `Compliance signal:`, `Project practice:`, `Industry:`,
  `Pitfalls:`, `GOOD`, `BAD`, `Steps`, `Anti-patterns`,
  `Skeleton`, `When to use what`, `Decision order`
- The verbatim content of any ``` fenced code block in playbook
  seeds — copy the seed exactly, do not translate inside fences
- Section names referenced cross-artifact (e.g.
  `## CORRECTNESS & CONSISTENCY (must-fix)`,
  `## GAP (must fill before implement)`,
  `## CONFLICT (must resolve before implement)`)

Out of doubt: prefer English. If a term shows up in the project's
`.harness/knowledge/glossary.md` with a Chinese gloss, use that
gloss; otherwise leave the English form.

This contract overrides any conflicting "translate everything"
instinct from the agent's general training.

