## 3. Verification

### 3.1 init.sh — the entry script

`./init.sh` at the project root is the **single command an agent
runs at session start**. It:

1. Prints a project summary (profile, flow, lang, current spec)
2. Runs environment health checks (deps, git status, tool versions)
3. Calls `.harness/scripts/{{ script_shell }}/verify.sh`

If `init.sh` is red, **repair it before adding new scope**.

### 3.2 verify.sh — the deterministic sensor

`.harness/scripts/{{ script_shell }}/verify.sh` is the single source
of truth for "is the build green". It is invoked identically by:

- editor / agent hooks
- `pre-commit`
- CI (`.gitlab-ci.yml`)
- `init.sh`

No two sensors can disagree about the build. If you need a faster
mode for a hook, that's a flag (`--fast`) on the same script —
not a parallel script.

### 3.3 Definition of Done

A feature is `passing` only when **all** of the following are true:

- [ ] Target behavior is implemented
- [ ] `verification` command actually ran green
- [ ] `evidence` recorded in `feature_list.json`
- [ ] `init.sh` still green at session end
- [ ] `session-handoff.md` updated (see § 5)

